Κατακθονίοις\">[Κ(ατακθονίοις)]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Θρεπτύλος\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Θρεπτύλος\">Θρεπτύλο[ς]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔζησεν\">[ἔζησεν]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"μῆνας\">μῆνας\u003C/span> [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>· \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\">Εὐφροσύνη\u003C/span>\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-text=\"μήτηρ\">μήτηρ\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-text=\"Θεοῖς\">Θ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"Κατακθονίοις\">[..]\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Θρεπτύλος\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Θρεπτύλος\">ΘΡΕΠΤΥΛΟ[.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔζησεν\">......]\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"μῆνας\">ΜΗΝΑΣ\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\">ΕΥΦΡΟΣΥΝΗ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-text=\"μήτηρ\">ΜΗΤΗΡ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001300_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001300_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001300.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001300-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"4\">4: \u003Cspan>Kaibel: μήτηρ [ἐποίησεν] (but the inscription seems to be intact in the last line)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>To the underworld spirits. Threptylos lived for [---] months. His mother Euphrosyne (made it).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Agli Dei inferi. Threptylos visse [---] mesi. Sua madre Euphrosyne (realizzò).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph presents the traditional structure recurring in many pagan epitaphs from Catania: a main sentence with the name of the deceased and his/her age, followed by a second sentence with the name of the dedicant with an attribute qualifying his/her relationship with the deceased. The dedication verb is often omitted, as in this case (Korhonen 2004: 85-87). The name \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θρεπτύλος\u003C/span> is not attested elsewhere, whereas in imperial times \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θρεπτός\u003C/span> is well attested (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">Threptus\u003C/span> in two inscriptions from Lilybaion: CIL 10.7243 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000523\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000523\u003C/a>, Silvestrini (2014) 220-223 no.4 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003459\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003459\u003C/a>, see LGPN 3a: 213). \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θρεπτύλος\u003C/span> seems to be a diminutive (with the suffix -\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ύλος\u003C/span>) of the better-known \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θρεπτός\u003C/span>, considering also the very young age of the deceased (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">μῆνας\u003C/span>).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">477\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Hoffmann 1904 5240 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 137 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 85-87 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Lunate Ε, Θ, Σ, cursive Μ, Φ with a long vertical stroke, ΝΗ in ligature. Occasional presence of interpuncts (triangular).\u003C/p> Lines 1-4  11-14  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not recorded  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[238,241,244,247,250,252,255,258,261],{"id":239,"html":240},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>· \u003Cspan data-text=\"Θεοῖς\">Θ(εοῖς)\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"Κατακθονίοις\">[Κ(ατακθονίοις)]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Θρεπτύλος\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Θρεπτύλος\">Θρεπτύλο[ς]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔζησεν\">[ἔζησεν]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"μῆνας\">μῆνας\u003C/span> [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>· \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\">Εὐφροσύνη\u003C/span>\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-text=\"μήτηρ\">μήτηρ\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-text=\"Θεοῖς\">Θ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"Κατακθονίοις\">[..]\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Θρεπτύλος\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Θρεπτύλος\">ΘΡΕΠΤΥΛΟ[.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔζησεν\">......]\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"μῆνας\">ΜΗΝΑΣ\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\">ΕΥΦΡΟΣΥΝΗ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-text=\"μήτηρ\">ΜΗΤΗΡ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":242,"html":243},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001300_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001300_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001300.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001300-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":245,"html":246},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"4\">4: \u003Cspan>Kaibel: μήτηρ [ἐποίησεν] (but the inscription seems to be intact in the last line)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":248,"html":249},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>To the underworld spirits. Threptylos lived for [---] months. His mother Euphrosyne (made it).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":248,"html":251},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Agli Dei inferi. Threptylos visse [---] mesi. Sua madre Euphrosyne (realizzò).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":253,"html":254},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph presents the traditional structure recurring in many pagan epitaphs from Catania: a main sentence with the name of the deceased and his/her age, followed by a second sentence with the name of the dedicant with an attribute qualifying his/her relationship with the deceased. The dedication verb is often omitted, as in this case (Korhonen 2004: 85-87). The name \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θρεπτύλος\u003C/span> is not attested elsewhere, whereas in imperial times \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θρεπτός\u003C/span> is well attested (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">Threptus\u003C/span> in two inscriptions from Lilybaion: CIL 10.7243 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000523\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000523\u003C/a>, Silvestrini (2014) 220-223 no.4 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003459\" target=\"_blank\">ISic003459\u003C/a>, see LGPN 3a: 213). \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θρεπτύλος\u003C/span> seems to be a diminutive (with the suffix -\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ύλος\u003C/span>) of the better-known \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Θρεπτός\u003C/span>, considering also the very young age of the deceased (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">μῆνας\u003C/span>).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":256,"html":257},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">477\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Hoffmann 1904 5240 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 137 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 85-87 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":259,"html":260},"handnote","\u003Cp>Lunate Ε, Θ, Σ, cursive Μ, Φ with a long vertical stroke, ΝΗ in ligature. Occasional presence of interpuncts (triangular).\u003C/p> Lines 1-4  11-14  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not recorded  ",{"id":262,"html":263},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[265,267,270,271],{"html":266},"Text encoding: Marta Fogagnolo",{"id":268,"lang":130,"html":269},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>· \u003Cspan data-text=\"Θεοῖς\">Θ(εοῖς)\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"Κατακθονίοις\">[Κ(ατακθονίοις)]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Θρεπτύλος\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Θρεπτύλος\">Θρεπτύλο[ς]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔζησεν\">[ἔζησεν]\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"μῆνας\">μῆνας\u003C/span> [\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>· \u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\">Εὐφροσύνη\u003C/span>\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-text=\"μήτηρ\">μήτηρ\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":266},{"id":272,"lang":130,"html":273},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-text=\"Θεοῖς\">Θ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"Κατακθονίοις\">[..]\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Θρεπτύλος\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Θρεπτύλος\">ΘΡΕΠΤΥΛΟ[.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔζησεν\">......]\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"μῆνας\">ΜΗΝΑΣ\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐφροσύνη\">ΕΥΦΡΟΣΥΝΗ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-text=\"μήτηρ\">ΜΗΤΗΡ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[275,277],{"image":106,"thumb":276,"title":109},"ISic001300_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":278,"thumb":279,"t